## bottleneck.detected - Pentagon handoff message does not auto-activate Code Owner

frame: t4-openai-tool-shape-translation
complexity: extra-hard
source: Pentagon conversation-debug logs + process list
symptom: Theo sent the red-test handoff to Maya (Code Owner), but no Maya
  'executeAgentTurn' or 'codex exec' worker appeared afterward. Pentagon UI
  stayed alive; only the Pentagon app process was running.
owner: Avery (Frame Architect) + Riley (Evidence Lead)
feedback_action: Treat direct 'send_message' as context delivery only unless a
  recipient turn is observed in logs. Require an explicit activation step or
  visible worker process before claiming an owner is working.
evidence:
  - "Theo sent handoff to conversation 0d996a94-45a6-4ef6-b8bd-45bc3f84d7e1 at 2026-05-22T16:20:27Z."
  - "T4 red-test commit: inner:7c319cf."
  - "Targeted pytest before implementation: 10 failed, 2 passed."
  - "Post-handoff process check: Pentagon app alive, no codex exec / pytest / Maya worker."
  - "Fallback implementation landed by Codex at inner:b8eb508 and inner:612ac0a after activation gap; this is not counted as Maya autonomous completion."

## bottleneck.detected - Pentagon default model drifted after agent model patch

frame: pentagon-reliability-repair
complexity: all
source: macOS defaults
symptom: Workspace default still read claude-opus-4-7[1m] even after the live
  per-agent model audit said agents were patched to gpt-5.5. New agents could
  inherit the wrong model.
owner: Avery (Frame Architect) + Riley (Evidence Lead)
feedback_action: Set run.pentagon.app pentagon.defaultModel to gpt-5.5 and
  require model refresh audit before T5 starts.
evidence:
  - "Before: defaults read run.pentagon.app pentagon.defaultModel -> claude-opus-4-7[1m]"
  - "After: defaults read run.pentagon.app pentagon.defaultModel -> gpt-5.5"

